    adaptor.read(&data.value);
    adaptor.read(&data.ratio);

    return data;
}
```

The implementation uses:
- `buffer_write_adaptor` to wrap the vector for writing
- Template `write(auto& source)` method to write each field type-safely
- `buffer_read_adaptor` to wrap the vector for reading  
- Template `read(T* destination)` method to read into each field
- Fields are written/read in the same order (id → value → ratio)

The buffer adaptors handle the byte-level serialization automatically while maintaining type safety through the template methods.

